      "output": "{\n  \"search_id\": \"search_edbcaefff75d44aea0facda82c92d0e4\",\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://visitbirmingham.com/listing/hyatt-regency-birmingham/20595101\",\n      \"title\": \"Hyatt Regency Birmingham\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"# 301 Moved Permanently\\n\\n* * *\\n\\nopenresty\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.hyatt.com/hyatt-regency/en-US/birmi-hyatt-regency-birmingham/parking-and-transportation\",\n      \"title\": \"Map, Parking & Directions  | Hyatt Regency Birmingham\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Skip Main Navigation\\n\\n[World of Hyatt](https://www.hyatt.com)\\n\\n* Language\\n*\\n\\nHyatt Regency Birmingham\\n\\nLocations Book\\n\\nLocations Book\\n\\nSite Menu Locations\\n\\nHyatt Regency Birmingham\\n\\n* Home\\n* Rooms & Suites\\n* Exclusive Offers\\n* Dining\\n* Events & Attractions\\n* Meetings & Events\\n* Weddings & Celebrations\\n* Hotel Information\\n* Parking & Transportation\\n* Hotel Policies\\n* Gallery\\n* Reviews\\n* [Amala Spa](https://www.hyatt.com/en-US/spas/Amala-Spa/about)\\n* About Hyatt Regency\\n\\nHyatt Regency Birmingham\\n\\n[2 Bridge Street, Birmingham, B1 2JZ, United Kingdom](https://maps.google.com/?q=Hyatt%20Regency%20Birmingham%2BB1%202JZ)\\n\\nPhone Number Tel: \\\\+44 121 643 1234\\n\\n[4\\\\.0 (2182 Reviews)](https://www.hyatt.com/hyatt-regency/en-US/birmi-hyatt-regency-birmingham/reviews \\\"The score is calculated based on the score guests provided after completing stays.\\\")\\n\\nHyatt Regency Birmingham\\n\\n[Map](https://maps.google.com/?q=Hyatt%20Regency%20Birmingham%2BB1%202JZ) [4\\\\.0](https://www.hyatt.\\ncom/hyatt-regency/en-US/birmi-hyatt-regency-birmingham/reviews \\\"The score is calculated based on the score guests provided after completing stays.\\\")\\n\\nBook\\n\\n# Parking & Transportation\\n\\n## Parking\\n\\n### Self Parking\\n\\nLimited car parking is available at the hotel on a first-come, first-served basis. Guests can pay for parking on arrival for the duration of their stay via the payment kiosk located beside the hotel entrance (outside of the building to the right of the entrance), via the YourParkingSpace app or by mobile service. Details can be found on signage throughout the car park.\\nImportant: Our hotel parking is protected using automatic number plate recognition (ANPR) technology. Please enter the correct registration during payment to avoid receiving a penalty or parking charge notice (PCN). In the event the car park is full when you arrive, Hyatt Regency Birmingham advises our guests to use the following secure parking facilities, located a short walk from the hotel.\\n\\nPer day\\n### Blucher Street\\n\\nThe off-street car park is located 0.08 kilometers / 0.05 miles from the hotel.\\n\\n### Mailbox Q-Park\\n\\nNearby self-parking located at B1 1RD\\n\\n### Q-Park Brindleyplace\\n\\nNearby self-parking located at 1 Brunswick Street\\n\\n## Transportation\\n\\nGetting here\\n\\nBirmingham Airport (BHX)\\n\\nBirmingham New Street Station\\n\\nShow Map\\n\\nClose Map\\n\\n## Hyatt Regency Birmingham\\n\\n[2 Bridge Street, Birmingham, B1 2JZ, United Kingdom](https://maps.google.com/?q=Hyatt%20Regency%20Birmingham)\\n\\nTel: \\\\+44 121 643 1234 Fax: \\\\+44 121 616 2323\\n\\n* Hotel Policies\\n\\n### Social\\n\\n* [Facebook](http://www.facebook.com/pages/Hyatt-Regency-Birmingham/267978088103)\\n* [Pinterest](https://www.pinterest.com/HyattBirmingham/)\\n* [Instagram](https://www.instagram.com/hyattbirmingham/)\\n* [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/company/hyatt-regency-birmingham)\\n\\n* Hotel Policies\\n\\n[](https://go.hyatt.com/link/v2/pcr__dkz-150VwLrMgqsK2v-wdn1IdJfoSXbS)\\n\\nEarn up to 60,000 Bonus Points\\n\\nwith the World of Hyatt Credit Card\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hyatt_Regency_Birmingham\",\n      \"title\": \"Hyatt Regency Birmingham - Wikipedia\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2025-10-25\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Hotel in Birmingham, England\\n\\n|Hyatt Regency Birmingham |\\n| --- | --- |\\n| |\\n|Interactive map of Hyatt Regency Birmingham |\\n|General information |\\n|Type |Hotel |\\n|Location |2 Bridge Street, Birmingham, B1 2JZ, England |\\n|Coordinates |[52°28′40″N 1°54′32″W ﻿ / ﻿ 52\\\\.4779°N 1.9089°W ﻿ / 52\\\\.4779; -1.9089](https://geohack.toolforge.org/geohack.php?pagename=Hyatt_Regency_Birmingham&params=52.4779_N_1.9089_W_region:GB-BIR_type:landmark) |\\n|Completed |1990 |\\n|Management |Hyatt Hotels Corporation |\\n|Technical details |\\n|Floor count |24 |\\n|Lifts/elevators |4 |\\n|Other information |\\n|Number of rooms |319 |\\n|Number of bars |1 |\\n|Website |\\n|[birmingham.regency.hyatt.com](https://birmingham.regency.hyatt.com/hyatt/hotels/index.jsp) |\\n\\nThe **Hyatt Regency Birmingham** is a hotel on Broad Street in the city centre of Birmingham , England . Hyatt Regency Birmingham stands at a height of 75 metres (246 feet) 24 floors [[ 1 ]]() and has 319 guest rooms.\\n[[ 2 ]]() The hotel, which opened in July 1990, [[ 3 ]]() has a blue glass exterior facade, and stands across the road from the International Convention Centre . [[ 4 ]]()\\n\\nThe hotel was built, and is run by, Hyatt Regency Birmingham Ltd. This company is a public-sector/private-sector partnership between the Hyatt Corporation , Trafalgar House\\\") , and Birmingham City Council . [[ 5 ]]() The hotel cost £37 million to build, with £1.5 million of that being provided by the city, which also donated the building site, which was, according to estimates, worth £615,000 in 1987. [[ 6 ]]() In June 1991, the Hyatt accommodated members of the International Olympic Committee , who were attending its 97th annual session at the International Convention Centre. [[ 7 ]]() In April 2002, the company (with the NEC Group as the third majority shareholder, after the demise of Trafalgar House) put the hotel building up for sale.\\n[[ 2 ]]() In November 2002, the hotel was sold to London Plaza Hotels for £27.5 million, with Hyatt Regency Birmingham Ltd continuing to operate it. [[ 8 ]]() Birmingham City Council made a £5 million profit on the sale, from its 17.5% stake in the hotel, which it used to pay off debt. [[ 9 ]]()\\n\\n The lounge and dining area of the Presidential Suite, home to the Prime Minister during the Conservative Party conference.\\n\\nThe hotel was specifically constructed to have close ties to the International Convention Centre, including a private-access bridge that joins the two. [[ 9 ]]() [[ 10 ]]() This easy to secure link was one factor in attracting the 24th G8 summit to the city, [[ 9 ]]() as well as the 2000 NATO Meeting of Defence Ministers. [[ 11 ]]() [[ 12 ]]() [[ 13 ]]()\\n\\nThe Hyatt Hotels Corporation bought the hotel out of administration in 2012 for £27 million.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.travelprofy.com/birmingham-new-street-station/hyatt-regency-birmingham\",\n      \"title\": \"Birmingham New Street Station to Hyatt Regency Birmingham - Travel Modes & Distance: Car, Public Transport\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Travelprofy\\n\\n# From 📍 Birmingham New Street Station, United Kingdom to ➡️ Hyatt Regency Birmingham, United Kingdom\\n\\nCalculate Distance\\n\\nGet ready for a fun trip from **Birmingham New Street, 6a 7a, Chinese Quarter, Digbeth, Attwood Green, Birmingham, West Midlands Combined Authority, England, B2 4PX, United Kingdom** to **Hyatt Regency Hotel, 2, Bridge Street, Ladywood, Park Central, Birmingham, West Midlands Combined Authority, England, B1 2JZ, United Kingdom** . This journey is great for friends or family who like taking turns driving or traveling together.\\n\\nHow far? Driving distance is **2\\\\.17 kilometers** ( **1\\\\.35 miles** )\\n\\nHow long? About **6 min** by car\\n\\nWalking time: **26 minutes** (based on an average walking speed of 5 km/h)\\n