  \\n  Birmingham Yardley\\n  \\n  [Book Now](https://www.travelodge.co.uk/hotels/111/Birmingham-Yardley-hotel \\\"Book Travelodge Birmingham Yardley\\\")\\n* hotel image\\n  \\n  Birmingham Fort Dunlop\\n[Book Now](https://www.travelodge.co.uk/hotels/304/Birmingham-Fort-Dunlop-hotel \\\"Book Travelodge Birmingham Fort Dunlop\\\")\\n* hotel image\\n  \\n  Birmingham Maypole\\n  \\n  [Book Now](https://www.travelodge.co.uk/hotels/617/Birmingham-Maypole-hotel \\\"Book Travelodge Birmingham Maypole\\\")\\n* hotel image\\n  \\n  West Bromwich\\n  \\n  [Book Now](https://www.travelodge.co.uk/hotels/621/West-Bromwich-hotel \\\"Book Travelodge West Bromwich\\\")\\n* hotel image\\n  \\n  Birmingham Sheldon\\n  \\n  [Book Now](https://www.travelodge.co.uk/hotels/445/Birmingham-Sheldon-hotel \\\"Book Travelodge Birmingham Sheldon\\\")\\n\\n## The heart of the action at Birmingham New Street Station\\n\\n### As Birmingham's biggest and most-used station, New Street is centred in the heart of the city. It's a ten-minute walk to the Mailbox, while upstairs, the station is connected to the Bullring by a corridor.\\n\\n## Enjoy retail therapy at Grand Central\\n### When Birmingham unveiled its brand-new New Street Station, it also introduced another fantastic shopping destination to the city: Grand Central. With over 40 shops and 20 restaurants, it's a shopping and lifestyle hub perfect for browsing while you're waiting for your train.\\n\\n## London in less than 90 minutes\\n\\n### Birmingham's well known for its great transport connections across the UK, and from New Street you can get almost anywhere in the country. London is less than an hour and a half away, with some trains reaching Euston in just over an hour - perfect for a day trip to Big Ben and the Houses of Parliament.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/FAQ_Answers-g186402-d193219-t3081731-How_far_is_the_hotel_from_New_street_station.html\",\n      \"title\": \"How far is the hotel from New street station - Tripadvisor\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Derby, United Kingdom 0 Votes The hotel is within 15 minutes walk from the station at a steady pace, hope this is helpful over a year ago\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.laterooms.com/hotels/birmingham-new-street-station-ed630\",\n      \"title\": \"The best hotel deals near Birmingham New Street Station from £37\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"The best hotel deals near Birmingham New Street Station from £37\\nCheck in to the Grand Hotel Birmingham, which is around a five-minute walk to the Grand Central Shopping Centre and Birmingham New Street Station.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.easyhotel.com/explore/hotels-near-new-street-station\",\n      \"title\": \"Hotels near New Street Station, Birmingham\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Deals Explore Help\\n\\nGBP (£)\\n\\n##### Select Currency\\n\\n* GBP - Pound sterling\\n* USD - U.S. Dollar\\n* EUR - Euro\\n* CHF - Swiss franc\\n* AED - Dirham\\n* BRL - Brazilian Real\\n* CAD - Canadian Dollar\\n* RUB - Russian Ruble\\n* PLN - Polish złoty\\n* SEK - Swedish Krona\\n* AUD - Australian Dollar\\n* INR - Indian Rupee\\n* HUF - Hungarian Forint\\n\\nLog in Sign up\\n\\nExplore\\n\\n* Deals\\n* Explore\\n* Help\\n\\n* * *\\n\\nSettings\\n\\n* Language\\n  \\n  English Flag\\n  \\n  English\\n* Price display\\n  \\n  GBP £\\n\\n# Hotels near New Street Station\\n\\nBirmingham\\n\\nRight in the heart of [Birmingham](https://www.easyhotel.com/hotels/united-kingdom/birmingham) , New Street Station is the city’s main transport hub, making it super easy to get in and out by train. It’s surrounded by great shopping, buzzing restaurants, and loads of entertainment, so staying nearby means you’re never far from the action. Whether you’re visiting for work, a weekend break, or just passing through, hotels near New Street Station are the perfect spot to base yourself.\\n## Birmingham City Centre\\n\\nBirmingham Airport - 25 mins by taxi\\n\\nBirmingham New Street Station - 3 mins walk\\n\\nBirmingham coach station - 15 min walk\\n\\nExplore Hotel\\n\\n[**easyHotel Birmingham City Centre**](https://www.easyhotel.com/hotels/united-kingdom/birmingham/birmingham-city-centre) is only 0.2 miles from New Street Station - that’s just a quick 5-minute stroll. You’ll find us on John Bright Street, surrounded by lively bars, tasty places to eat, and some of Birmingham’s top sights. Our rooms are simple, clean, and comfy - ideal for getting a good night’s sleep after a busy day. With great value prices and 24-hour reception, we make city stays easy, whether you’re here for a show, a shopping trip, or an early train the next day.\\n\\n## Why Stay Near New Street Station, Birmingham?\\n\\nStaying near New Street Station makes everything a breeze. You’re just a short walk from the Bullring & Grand Central for shopping, plus the Birmingham Hippodrome and O2 Academy for top nights out.\\nFancy something tasty? Chinatown is nearby, packed with brilliant food spots. And with trains running all over the UK, you can get to London, Manchester or the airport in no time. It’s the ideal location to make the most of Birmingham without wasting a minute.\\n\\n[Part of thefamily of brands](https://easy.com)\\n\\nSubscribe to get the latest hotel deals and offers by email. I agree to receive marketing and promotion emails from easyHotel UK Limited and it’s group subsidiary companies as referenced in our website privacy policy\\n\\nSubscribe\\n\\nDownload Apps\\n\\n[](https://apps.apple.com/gb/app/easyhotel/id1492316252?mt=8) [](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.easyhotelapp.app&hl=en&pcampaignid=MKT-Other-global-all-co-prtnr-py-PartBadge-Mar2515-1)\\n\\nSite Map Terms & Conditions Cookie Policy Privacy Policy\\n\\nGive us a follow:\\n\\n[](https://www.facebook.com/easyHotel)\\n\\n[](