      "code": "{\"query\": \"walk \\\"New Street Station\\\" Birmingham \\\"Broad Street\\\" \\\"Bridge Street\\\" directions pedestrian\"}",
      "output": "{\n  \"search_id\": \"search_9c719d255ce34f329fdc60e35249bdfd\",\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"http://hortons.co.uk/portfolio/piccadilly-arcade\",\n      \"title\": \"Piccadilly Arcade | Hortons\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-04-24\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"[Hortons Estate](https://hortons.co.uk) [Hortons Estate](https://hortons.co.uk)\\n\\n# Piccadilly Arcade\\n\\nBirmingham\\n\\nRetail\\n\\n### **Originally designed by Nicol & Nicol in the early 1900s, Piccadilly Arcade was one of Birmingham’s first cinemas before being converted into a ground floor retail arcade and basement bar.**\\n\\nThis charming shopping destination embraces its roots and history with artistic ceiling murals, an attractive sloped floor, and the classic uniform appearance of many of the original shop fronts.\\n\\nThe Arcade is adjacent to Birmingham New Street Station, bridging New Street and Stephenson Street.\\n\\n[Visit the website](https://piccadillyarcade.org/) [View on map](https://goo.gl/maps/rpy7vKc8NHiFfy4Z8)\\n\\n#### Project Overview:\\n\\n18\\n\\nRetail units\\n\\n22,250 sq ft\\n\\n#### Availability\\n\\n|Unit 12 |200 sq ft | |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n\\n[Visit the website](https://piccadillyarcade.org/) [View on map](https://goo.gl/maps/rpy7vKc8NHiFfy4Z8)\\n\\n### Tenant Quote:\\nWe’ve got to know many of our customers so well that they are on first-name terms and we consider them friends. It’s more than just a job: I enjoy going in daily. We’re all independent traders in the Arcade and we support each other, too, so it feels like a really great community. It makes sense to stay here.\\n\\n**Geoff Lam, Owner**\\n\\nFaculty Coffee\\n\\n* [About Us](https://hortons.co.uk/about-us/)\\n* [News](https://hortons.co.uk/news/)\\n* Portfolio\\n* [Contact](https://hortons.co.uk/contact-us/)\\n\\nShareholder Login\\n\\n### Get in touch\\n\\ne. mail@hortons.co.uk t. 0121 236 6481\\n\\n15 Colmore Row,  \\nBirmingham, B3 2BH\\n\\n### Follow us\\n\\n[](https://www.instagram.com/hortonsestate) [](https://twitter.com/hortonsestate) [](https://www.linkedin.com/company/hortons%27-estate-limited/)\\n\\nBack to top\\n\\nHortons Estate\\n\\n[Accessibility](https://hortons.co.uk/accessibility/) [Privacy policy](https://hortons.co.uk/privacy-policy/) [Cookie Policy](https://hortons.co.uk/cookie-policy/)\\n\\n[](https://www.barques.co.\\nuk/digital/seo)\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"http://fhp.co.uk/properties/35-37-stephenson-street\",\n      \"title\": \"35-37 Stephenson Street - FHP | Birmingham | To Let | FHP\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Busy pedestrian route between New Steet Station and\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"http://siddalljones.com/property/jubilee-centre-130-pershore-street-birmingham-b5-6nd\",\n      \"title\": \"Jubilee Centre, 130 Pershore Street, Birmingham, B5 6ND | Siddall Jones\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-05-26\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Applications must be submitted using the prescribed form and will be considered at the Landlord’s discretion.\\n\\n**Energy Performance Certificate**\\n\\nAvailable upon request from the agent.\\n\\n**Services**\\n\\nWe understand that the building has the benefit of all main services connected on, or adjacent to the subject property.  \\n  \\nThe agent has not tested the suitability of the connections and recommends that all interested parties carry out their own investigations as to their suitability.\\n\\n**Viewing**\\n\\nStrictly via the sole agent Siddall Jones.\\n\\n**Legal Costs**\\n\\nBoth parties are to bear their own legal and surveyor’s fees incurred during the transaction.\\n\\n**VAT**\\n\\nAll prices quoted are exclusive of VAT, which we understand is payable.\\n\\n## Accommodation\\n\\n|Name/Floor |Sq Ft |Sq M |Availability |Rent |\\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\\n|unit First Floor- 103 |680 |63\\\\.17 |Available |£11.63 per Sq Ft |\\n|unit First Floor 105 |1,294 |120\\\\.22 |Coming Soon |£11.68 per Sq Ft |\\n|unit First Floor - 107 |1,737 |161\\\\.37 |Available |£17.41 per Sq Ft |\\n|unit First Floor- 113 |2,320 |215\\\\.53 |Coming Soon |£11.68 per Sq Ft |\\n|unit Second Floor- 213 |900 |83\\\\.61 |Coming Soon |£11.67 per Sq Ft |\\n|unit Third Floor 311 |1,858 |172\\\\.61 |Available |£17.40 per Sq Ft |\\n|unit Third Floor - 313 |1,840 |170\\\\.94 |Available |£11.68 per Sq Ft |\\n|unit 316 |1,600 |148\\\\.64 |Coming Soon |£11.69 per Sq Ft |\\n|unit Second Floor- 204 |1,303 |121\\\\.05 |Occupied |£11.68 per Sq Ft |\\n|unit Second Floor- 205 |1,567 |145\\\\.58 |Occupied |£11.68 per Sq Ft |\\n|unit Third Floor - 317A |291 |27\\\\.03 |Occupied |£11.71 per Sq Ft |\\n|unit First Floor- 114 |1,443 |134\\\\.06 |Occupied |£11.64 per Sq Ft |\\n|**Total** |**16,833** |**1,563.84** | | |\\n\\n## Location\\n\\nThe property is ideally located on Pershore Street, just a few minutes' walk from Birmingham's New Street Station, in the heart of Southside — one of the city’s most vibrant and diverse districts.\\nThis area, home to Chinatown, the Gay Quarter, and the Theatre District, boasts a lively mix of bars, restaurants, and shops.  \\n  \\nRecent residential developments have revitalised the area, attracting independent businesses eager to join this thriving community. The property is perfectly positioned to be part of the area's success, just a short walk from major landmarks like the ICC, Symphony Hall, NIA, Hippodrome, Alexandra Theatres, and the Bullring Shopping Centre.  \\n  \\nPershore Street is a key road connecting to the city centre and surrounding areas. The A38(M) Aston Expressway lies approximately 1 mile to the north, this major road provides direct access to the M6 motorway, facilitating travel to the north and south.\\n\\n## Request a viewing\\n\\nContact us for more information or to arrange a viewing\\n\\n### Edward Siddall-Jones\\n\\n0121 638 0500  \\n07803 571 891\\n\\n### Sophie Froggatt\\n\\n0121 638 0500  \\n07842013854\\n\\n### Ryan Lynch\\n\\n0121 638 0500  \\n07710022800\\n\\n### Scott Rawlings\\n\\n0121 638 0500\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Street%2C_Birmingham\",\n      \"title\": \"New Street, Birmingham - Wikipedia\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-02-22\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Street in Birmingham, United Kingdom\\n\\nFor the railway station, see Birmingham New Street railway station .\\n\\n|\\n\\nNew Street and Corporation Street |\\n| --- | --- |\\n|Interactive map of New Street |\\n|Length |500 m (1,600 ft) |\\n|Location |Birmingham |\\n|Postal code |B2 |\\n|East end |Rotunda Square  \\n[52°27′27″N 1°53′42″W ﻿ / ﻿ 52\\\\.457567°N 1.895033°W ﻿ / 52\\\\.457567; -1.895033](https://geohack.toolforge.org/geohack.php?pagename=New_Street,_Birmingham&params=52.457567_N_1.895033_W_) |\\n|West end |Victoria Square  \\n[52°28′46″N 1°54′08″W ﻿ / ﻿ 52\\\\.479486°N 1.902204°W ﻿ / 52\\\\.479486; -1.902204](https://geohack.toolforge.org/geohack.php?pagename=New_Street,_Birmingham&params=52.479486_N_1.902204_W_) |\\n\\n**New Street** is a street in central Birmingham , England. It is one of the city's principal thoroughfares and shopping streets linking Victoria Square to the Bullring Shopping Centre .\\nIt gives its name to New Street railway station , although the station has never had direct access to New Street except via Stephenson Place and latterly Grand Central shopping centre .\\n\\n## History\\n\\n [edit ]\\n\\nNew Street is first mentioned as _novus vicus_ in the surviving borough rental records of 1296, at which point it was partly built upon with burgage plots, [[ 1 ]]() but was also the site of most of the few open fields remaining within the borough, including _Barlycroft_ , _Stoctonesfeld_ and _Wodegrene_ . [[ 2 ]]() It is mentioned again, this time as _le Newestret_ in the rentals of 1344–45. [[ 3 ]]() The street may have been created at the time of the establishment of Birmingham's market in 1166, as a more direct route from the centre of the new town at the Bull Ring to the home of the de Birmingham family 's feudal overlords at Dudley Castle . [[ 4 ]]()\\nThe street underwent large development during the 18th and 19th century and in an 1840s guide, shortly after the building of the Town Hall it is described as \\\" _the Bond Street of Birmingham; what with its glittering array of shops, its inns; its fine Elizabethan School, its School of Arts, its Theatre, its Post-office, it gives the tone to that part of the town._ \\\"\\n\\nIn 1974, the Birmingham pub bombings took place in two pubs on New Street; one inside King Edward House, the other under the Rotunda\\\") . A total of 21 people died as a result of their injuries in these blasts. [[ 5 ]]()\\n\\n### Lost buildings\\n\\n [edit ]\\n\\n New Street c. 1825 , by Henry Harris. Also looking west.  Charles Barry's Free Grammar School  The Theatre Royal in 1780\\n\\n* Free Grammar School , originally the Guild of the Holy Cross\\\") . Rebuilt twice on this site and then moved to Edgbaston in 1939 resulting in the demolition of the Charles Barry building.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"http://invest.jll.com/us/en/listings/retail/piccadilly-arcade-birmingham\",\n      \"title\": \"Piccadilly Arcade, Birmingham - Properties for Sale | US | JLL\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-05-20\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Piccadilly Arcade comprises a well let prime retail & leisure scheme with asset management potential, located at the heart of Birmingham City Centre. The property is located in a highly strategic position fronting both New Street and Stephenson Street within the city's primary retail & leisure area.\\n\\nPiccadilly Arcade comprises a boutique retail & leisure destination extending to a total of 23,259 sq ft. Arranged over lower ground, ground and 4 upper floors the arcade provides an attractive retail environment with well-presented units featuring fully glazed shopfronts and decorative flooring and ceiling units.\\n\\n... Read more\\n\\n## Attributes\\n\\nBuilding area net\\n\\n23,259 sf\\n\\nOccupancy\\n\\n97%\\n\\n## Media\\n\\n11images\\n\\n## Investment highlights\\n\\n1. Strategically positioned at the heart of Birmingham with primary frontage to New Street, the city’s highest footfall area\\n2. Birmingham commands the UK’s second-largest primary retail catchment and total available spend\\n3.\\nBirmingham has the 2nd largest primary retail population catchment in the UK totalling 497,612 with a core catchment area of 1,001,753\\n4. Piccadilly Arcade is located directly adjacent to Birmingham New Street Station and Grand Central metro stop, delivering exceptional visibility, footfall and accessibility\\n5. The Arcade extends to 23,259 sq ft (2,160.7 sq m) of retail & leisure accommodation arranged as two large leisure units (Clays & Be At One) and 12 boutique arcade units\\n6. 97% let to 13 tenants, combining established operators with exciting new market entrants\\n7. Highly reversionary total rent of £626,000 per annum reflects a low average of £43 psf, providing considerable rental growth opportunity\\n8. Long dated weighted average unexpired lease term of 14.5 years to expiry, 9.1 years to break\\n9. 81% of total income derived from tenants presenting Low or Very Low risk of business failure\\n10.\\nStrong near term income growth potential, with 26% of rent subject to review in 2026-2027 and one vacant unit available for letting\\n11. The Be at One rent (£13.28 psf) is highly reversionary and subject to an outstanding rent review (March 2026). Comparables support rents of up to £50psf for similar leisure units\\n12. Diverse asset management strategies available through lettings, lease events, rent reviews and further repositioning\\n13. Freehold\\n\\nProposal\\n\\nWe are instructed to seek offers in excess of £5,750,000 subject to contract and exclusive of VAT.\\n\\nA purchase at this level reflects an attractive net initial yield of 10.21%, assuming standard purchasers costs.\\n\\n## Contact brokers\\n\\nPiccadilly Arcade, Birmingham (0 Properties)\\n\\n## Similar properties\\n\\nView more\\n\\nEND Clothing, 6-14 St Marys Gate, Manchester\\n\\nSt Mary's Gate, Manchester, M1 1PX, UK\\n\\n29,739 sf\\n\\nRetail\\n\\nDFS & Sofology, Wootton Bassett Road, Swindon\\n\\nWootton Bassett Road, Swindon, SN5 8WF\\n\\n$6,377,000 | 20,654 sf\\n\\nRetail\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://gb.mapometer.com/search_routes/walking/birmingham\",\n      \"title\": \"walking route finder: search by distance and location in ...\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Mapometer Search Engine - find walking routes in your area of Birmingham, UK. Find walking routes within a distance range in Birmingham. See the route map and elevation profile for each walking route.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://showmethejourney.com/train-travel-info/countries/great-britain/cities/birmingham/rail-stations/birmingham-new-street/\",\n      \"title\": \"Birmingham New Street (Birmingham) - ShowMeTheJourney\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"This guide to taking trains from and to Birmingham New Street focuses on the less obvious aspects of arriving and departing from this station by train. It encompasses a weight of detail, because how to take a train from Birmingham New Street is distinct, from any other station ShowMeTheJourney has ever used.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"http://tripadvisor.com/Attraction_Review-g186402-d21290515-Reviews-Piccadilly_Arcade-Birmingham_West_Midlands_England.html\",\n      \"title\": \"Piccadilly Arcade - All You SHOULD Know Before Going ...\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Connecting both Stephenson Street and New Street is Piccadilly Arcade\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.networkrail.co.uk/rail-travel/our-stations/birmingham-new-street/birmingham-new-street-station-map/\",\n      \"title\": \"Birmingham New Street station map - Network Rail\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Our interactive map to help you navigate around Birmingham New Street Station. From platforms to toilets, lifts and much more.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.routeyou.com/en-gb/route/planner/2\",\n      \"title\": \"Walking route planner - United Kingdom | RouteYou\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Plan your walking route along the most beautiful tracks of the United Kingdom. Print, download as GPS track and save it.\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"warnings\": null,\n  \"usage\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"sku_search\",\n      \"count\": 1\n    }\n  ],\n  \"session_id\": \"ses_154d062fcffe5nUIm97okDOMmY\"\n}",
