      "type": "answer",
      "text": "Based on the geography of Birmingham city centre, here's a step-by-step walkthrough:\n\n**Walking route: ~1.1 km / 13 minutes**\n\n1. **Exit the station** via the main entrance onto **Stephenson Street** (the Grand Central side)\n\n2. **Turn right** and walk along Stephenson Street toward the city centre\n\n3. **Continue onto New Street** — you'll pass the Bullring shopping centre on your left\n\n4. **Keep walking west** along New Street, passing through to **Paradise Street**\n\n5. **Continue onto Broad Street** — you'll pass Symphony Hall and the ICC (International Convention Centre) on your left\n\n6. **The Hyatt Regency** is the tall blue glass tower on your **right-hand side**, at the corner of **Bridge Street and Broad Street**\n\nThe hotel is the distinctive 24-storey blue building — hard to miss. The ICC is directly across the road from it.\n\n**Alternatively**, you can take the **West Midlands Metro tram** from Grand Central (above the station) to **Centenary Square** stop, which drops you right next to the hotel — about 5 minutes on the tram.",
      "timestamp": 1780988572791
    },
