      "type": "thought",
      "text": "I'm not getting detailed step-by-step walking directions from these searches. However, based on my knowledge of Birmingham city centre and the geographic coordinates, I can provide a reasonable walkthrough of the walking route from Birmingham New Street Station to the Hyatt Regency Birmingham.\n\nFrom the Rome2Rio data, the walking distance is about 3,750 feet (approximately 1.14 km) and takes about 13 minutes. The Hyatt Regency is on Broad Street / Bridge Street area, which is in the western part of the city centre near the ICC (International Convention Centre).\n\nLet me provide a sensible walking route based on the geography of Birmingham:\n\n\nThe most straightforward path would be to exit the station onto Stephenson Street, head west through the city centre past the Bullring and Victoria Square, then continue down Broad Street toward the ICC where the hotel sits at the junction with Bridge Street. Alternatively, there's a slightly shorter route via Paradise Street and Sheepcote Street that cuts through more directly.",
